T1  - Uncertainty and liquidity
AU  - Giovannini, Alberto
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 23
IS  - 2
SP  - 239
EP  - 258
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/03/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(89)90050-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393289900500
AB  - This paper studies a model where money is valued for the liquidity services it provides in the future. Changes in expectations of the value of future liquidity services affect the desired proportions of money and other assets in agents' portfolios, and, as a result, they change nominal interest rates and real stock prices. I find that changes in dividend risk have effects opposite to those in portfolio models without money. Furthermore, nominal interest rates are the best (least noisy) indicator of changes in uncertainty about future dividends.
ER  - 
